Reasoning: 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper focuses on proactive tile-based video streaming for virtual reality (VR) videos, which falls under the category of multimedia. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the communication aspect of proactive VR video streaming, specifically the need to match the prediction capability to the computing and communication capability. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper mentions two existing tile prediction methods, which may involve computer vision techniques. 
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper deals with VR video streaming, which involves graphics processing. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper aims to maximize the quality of experience (QoE) of watching a VR video, which is a key aspect of human-computer interaction.
